SYSTEM MIGRATION RULES — STAGE 1.7

The agent must follow these rules strictly:

1. Phases must be executed strictly in order A → K.
2. Never modify synthesis_agent.py until Phase K.
3. Never introduce additional LLM calls.
4. Each agent may perform only one LLM call.
5. Never introduce async execution or background workers.
6. Never implement retry logic in agents.
7. Canonical data must never be modified downstream of Agent 11.
8. Projection artifacts must remain pipeline-ephemeral and never persisted.
9. Validation checkpoints defined in the migration plan must be executed after each phase.
10. If a phase requires files outside the phase scope, stop execution and ask for review.